This is the protocol for a review and there is no abstract. The objectives are as follows:, The objectives of this systematic review are to evaluate the efficacy and safety of acupuncture therapy in patients with RLS., The following hypotheses are to be tested:, (1) acupuncture is more effective than placebo acupuncture, sham acupuncture or no treatment in treating RLS;, (2) acupuncture is more effective than western medicine or herbal medicine in treating RLS;, (3) there are less adverse effects in the acupuncture group than in the western medicine or herbal medicine group